      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The probability density function for the triangular distribution is"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "P(x;l, m, r) = \\begin{cases} \\frac{2(x-l)}{(r-l)(m-l)}& \\text{for $l \\leq x \\leq m$},\\\\ \\frac{2(r-x)}{(r-l)(r-m)}& \\text{for $m \\leq x \\leq r$},\\\\ 0& \\text{otherwise}. \\end{cases}"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The triangular distribution is often used in ill-defined\nproblems where the underlying distribution is not known, but\nsome knowledge of the limits and mode exists. Often it is used\nin simulations."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
